assumptions: A MOU exists between both countries to aim for a total export of 9000 MW from Laos to Thailand by 2030, however exact projects to faciliate these numbers have not been been specificied. The JICA report indicates that Thailand's autorities expect an increase in import of 700 MW every two years from all neighbouring countries combined (but not exactly how much from Laos). Furthermore, complicating factors such as ecology concerns affect the speed at which new hydro developments (and resulting imports) can be commissioned. Thailand's Power Purchase Plan 2023 which should be released soon might provide more insights on expected transmission developments on the short to medium term, however as of yet no concrete plans/values can be found so no new planned capacity has been added.

Following Table 6.2-12 and Table 6.2-13 in the JICA report, 2574 MW (970+869+735) of generating capacity (mostly hydro) is designated for export purposes to VNMCE by latest 2025 including transmission developments to support said exports. We assume that this equals the available transmission capacity by 2025 - the already existing 538 MW.  Given that these developments are specifically marked for export purposes with lines running from specific powerplants we assume that available transmission capacity is solely unidirectional. A MOU exists between both countries to export 5000 MW from Laos to Vietnam by 2030, however it is not specified to which parts of Vietnam this export is expected nor the status of developments post 2025 hence beyond the 2025 values we do not include any additional planned capacities.

Following Table 6.2-12 in the JICA report, 1032 ('Total' + HPP Nam Ou 3 210 MW) MW of generating capacity (mostly hydro) is designated for export purposes to VNMNO by latest 2025 including transmission developments to support said exports. We assume that this equals the available transmission capacity by 2025. Given that these developments are specifically marked for export purposes with lines running from specific powerplants we assume that available transmission capacity is solely unidirectional. A MOU exists between both countries to export 5000 MW from Laos to Vietnam by 2030, however it is not specified to which parts of Vietnam this export is expected nor the status of developments post 2025 hence beyond the 2025 values we do not include any additional planned capacities.
